<figureCitation box="[208,293,1436,1461]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1772,1794]" captionTargetBox="[154,1432,193,1750]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,193,1750]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 10. Apopyllus spp., epigynum, ventral view, drawings. Vulva can be seen by transparency. A A. silvestrii (MCTP 26293). B A. suavis (MNRJ 58361). C A. malleco (AMNH). D A. huanuco (AMNH). E A. now (MCZ 24971). F A. gandarela new. sp. (UFMG 16876). G A. centralis new sp. (UFMG 4564). H A. atlanticus new sp. (MCTP 27338)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261083/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="309">Figs 10</figureCitation>
C, 11C, 12C, 13C).
</paragraph>
